fields.description:
When we set the following in AndroidManifest.xml, the cursor does not show up in TextFields:
{code}<uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion="8" android:targetSdkVersion="16" />{code}

It seems that when the targetSdkVersion is set to 16, the cursor is not showing up.

comments.body:
We tested this issue with the test code below. We canâ€™t reproduce this issue with Titanium SDK 3.1.3GA. Please test this issue using the latest release and let us know your feedback. If you continue to get the reported error, please post us your test case and steps to reproduce. We will revisit it again.


 
h5. Testing Environment:
Ti CLI 3.1.2
Titanium SDK:3.0.2 and later
Android SDK: 4.1 and later
 
h5. Steps to Reproduce:
1.create a simple project.
2.Update this code in app.js and tiapp.xml
3.Then run this with testing environment.
4. Click on textfields
5. Cursor will shown well as we expected 
 
 
 h5. Test Case

app.js
 {code}
var win = Titanium.UI.createWindow({
	layout : 'vertical',
	title : 'TextField Test',
	navBarHidden : false
});
 
 
var text1 = Ti.UI.createTextField({
	height : Ti.UI.SIZE,
	top : 10,
	left : 10,
	width : Ti.UI.FILL,
	hintText : 'This is textField1',
	keyboardType : Ti.UI.KEYBOARD_DEFAULT,
	returnKeyType : Ti.UI.RETURNKEY_DEFAULT,
	borderStyle : Ti.UI.INPUT_BORDERSTYLE_ROUNDED
});
 
 
text1.addEventListener('return', function(e) {
	text1.blur();
	alert('Input was: ' + text1.value);
});
 
 
win.add(text1);
 
 
var text2 = Ti.UI.createTextField({
	height : Ti.UI.SIZE,
	top : 10,
	left : 10,
	width : Ti.UI.FILL,
	hintText : 'This is textField2',
	keyboardType : Ti.UI.KEYBOARD_DEFAULT,
	returnKeyType : Ti.UI.RETURNKEY_DEFAULT,
	borderStyle : Ti.UI.INPUT_BORDERSTYLE_ROUNDED
});
 
text2.addEventListener('return', function(e) {
	text2.blur();
	alert('Input was: ' + text2.value);
});
 
win.add(text2);
 
var text3 = Ti.UI.createTextField({
	height : Ti.UI.SIZE,
	top : 10,
	left : 10,
	width : Ti.UI.FILL,
	hintText : 'This is textField3',
	keyboardType : Ti.UI.KEYBOARD_DEFAULT,
	returnKeyType : Ti.UI.RETURNKEY_DEFAULT,
	borderStyle : Ti.UI.INPUT_BORDERSTYLE_ROUNDED
});
 
text3.addEventListener('return', function(e) {
	text3.blur();
	alert('Input was: ' + text3.value);
});
 
win.add(text3);
 
win.open();

{code}


tiapp.xml

{code}
<android xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android">
        <tool-api-level>16</tool-api-level>
        <manifest>
            <uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion="8" android:targetSdkVersion="16"/>
        </manifest>
    </android>
{code}

Please, reproduce this ticket on Ti SDK 3.2.0. It's not working for me.

h5. Environment:

Titanium Studio, build: 3.2.0.201312191547
Titanium SDK version 3.2.0.GA
CLI version 3.2.0
Aloy 1.3.0
Mac OSX: 10.9.1
Device: HTC One S, Android 4.1.1

h5. Step to Reproduce:

1. Create a simple project
2. Open file ApplicationWindow.js for Android
3. Update code
4. Run app
5. Click on text field
6. Cursor not show up

h5. Test case:

ApplicationWindow.js

{code}
//Application Window Component Constructor
function ApplicationWindow() {
	//load component dependencies
	var FirstView = require('ui/common/FirstView');

	//create component instance
	var self = Ti.UI.createWindow({
		backgroundColor:'#ffffff',
		navBarHidden:true,
		exitOnClose:true
	});

	//construct UI
	var firstView = new FirstView();
	self.add(firstView);


	var txt = Ti.UI.createTextField({
		top: 100,
		left: 100,
		width: 120,
		height: 40,
		color: 'red',
		borderWidth: 1,
		borderColor: 'blue'	
	});

	firstView.add(txt);

	return self;
}

//make constructor function the public component interface
module.exports = ApplicationWindow;
{code}

@Ritu Agrawal, my complete test case.

1. Create new simple project
2. Put code in app.js

{code}
var window = Ti.UI.createWindow({
	backgroundColor:'#ffffff',
	navBarHidden:true,
	exitOnClose:true
}),
view = Ti.UI.createView(),
textField = Ti.UI.createTextField({
    top: 100,
    left: 100,
    width: 120,
    height: 40,
    color: 'red',
    borderWidth: 1,
    borderColor: 'blue' 
});

view.add(textField);
window.add(view);
window.open();

{code}
